    Class for ISO 14443-3 transponder Infineon MIFARE Ultralight.

    Description:
    High-level class for easy-to-use Transponder specific communication. See ITagGroup for additional information.

    Note: Programmers should be familiar with the ISO 14443 standards.

    • Method Detail

      • authent

        public int authent(byte readerKeyIndex)
            throws FeException
        Authent Mifare Ultralight C with key from Reader
        Parameters:
        readerKeyIndex - Reader key index
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        [0xB2][0xB2] Authent Mifare with key from reader.
        This method is realized with Reader command [0xB2] ISO14443 Special Host Commands and only applicable, if the Transponder is in selected mode.
        Detailed description about the command and the parameters can be found in:
        - Product Datasheet for MIFARE Ultralight C from NXP Semiconductors
        - System Manual SoftCrypto Functions from FEIG ELECTRONIC
        The Transponder must be selected first with ITagGroup.tagSelect.
